Deputy mineral resources and energy minister Bavelile Hlongwa died in a car crash on Friday. While details of her death are still sketchy, it is believed that two other people were killed in the accident. The 38-year-old Hlongwa was appointed deputy minister on May 30 this year.  Taking to Twitter, Gauteng ANC passed on a brief message of condolences, confirming the news of Hlongwa's death, tweeting: "Death be not proud … We dip our head in mourning the tragic passing on of Comrade Bavelile Hlongwa who was killed together with two other people in a major crash on the N1 highway last night …"   